\end_inset

 show the errors resulted in comparing the input contact trace, and the
 contact trace resulted from the inferred mobility.As we can see these errors
 have some spikes in case of RPGM and is more smooth for RWP and DA.
 This is mostly due to the grouped nature of RPGM and presence of obvious
 communities in that.
 Also it's obvious that the errors for DA are much smaller than the other
 tow models.
 This is due to the fact that most nodes in DA model are wandering in a
 dense area, and number of connections are surprisingly high compared to
 the RWP and RPGM, resulting in a denser connectivity graph.
\end_layout

